HolyRooster ... 

I disagree with STJ11.

Everything I've seen and read about MW2 shows it to be the same basic CoD system, but the engine has been tweaked again, there is a new system for custom kill streaks, the weaponry has been greatly expanded, and there are lots of new toys that are worth buying the game for ... especially if you're a CoD fan like me.

Personally, I don't really like Halo, so the ODST for me is a no-go, but I wouldn't trade either ODST or Batman for MW2.  I can't help you decide between those two, but I can definitely say that going without MW2 would be a mistake.
